@Henry Su

Or, conversely, sometimes my mind seems to have fingers of its own. 

Bless its heart.

@Mike 
The pig ought to be careful, since they make sausage out of ground hog.


Unless it's emu sausage.  After all, they lay green eggs.

@Caroline 

Thank you, Caroline. When I got that answer, I was skeptical that it was a true Pooh quote. I read it to my husband, and he agreed it sounded like FauxPooh. 

I Googled the quote, and got a variety of hits, but not one of them mentioned the book or chapter from which it allegedly came.

@R.J. Smith

I had the SM (of COSMO) in that space, and I was sure something was wrong, because what drink has SM in the middle? Once I got the final O from the crosses, it was obvious. 

A COSMO is very low on my list of preferred cocktails.

@Keeylay Tehran 

I believe the "Five Burrows" in a literal sense relates to the 5 instances of the circled squares -- or holes -- in the grid.

I know that the constructor referenced NYC because of the pun on burrows/boroughs -- of which we have five. (And not because of any correlation between mole burrows and rat nests... Or rat holes!)






