I read the column more closely (only skimmed it before) and TIghTEned things up. Titer?  I just looked it up, and yup, TITER.

Well, this one took longer than usual, but the ride was worth it.  Loads of fun until I went off the rails. Thank you, Nathan Hasegawa.  You really whacked the mole for a great puzzle.

@Bruce 
I could have easily gone either way on EkG vs. ECG, but PRACTICE gave it away. Interesting that the former beats out the latter as xword answers (59 to 35), but ngram viewer shows greater use of ECG. See:

<a href="http://tinyurl.com/bfpjxf9v" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/bfpjxf9v</a>

